About this item

    This fits your .
  • Make sure this fits by entering your model number.
  • Unique Design: UGREEN USB-C to USB-A cable with an innovative 90 degrees L design, is much more convenient and more comfortable for playing games, watching videos, reading e-books when you lie on the couch or bed while charging. Note: For phone with a case, it supports Max 0.06 inch slim phone case.
  • Safe and Quick Charge: This USB 2.0 fast charging cable supports Quick Charge 2.0 and 3.0, with max output up to 3A, providing 5V 3A, 9V 2A or 12V 1.5A fast charge. With a built-in 56KΩ resistor, this type c charger guarantees reliable conductivity and charging, protecting your cell phones from damage due to excessive current.
  • Broad Compatibility: UGREEN type c charging cable is compatible with Samsung S20 S10 S10e S10 Plus Galaxy S9 S8 Plus Note 9 Note8 A8 2018, Galaxy Tab S3 9.7, Galaxy Fold, iPad Pro 11, 2018 iPad Pro 12.9, LG G5 G6 G7 G8 ThinQ, LG V20 V30 V40 V50, Motorola Razr 2019, Moto G7 G6, Moto Z force, Moto z2 play, Nintendo switch, compatible with GoPro Hero 5 hero 6 7 black, ZTE Axon 7, HTC 10 U12+, OnePlus 2, Huawei P9 and more.
  • Premium Quality: Nylon braided cable ensures reliability and durability. Double-sided USB C connectors with overmolded strain relief designed for frequent plugging and unplugging, provide a charger cable with reliable performance and longer lifespan. The security of charging is guaranteed by the built-in 56KΩ resistor from over voltage or over current.
  • What you get: 1x UGREEN Right Angle USB C to A Cable. Note: It's USB 2.0 charging cable.

Product Description

90 Degree Right Angle USB C to USB A Charger

With an innovative 90 degrees L design, UGREEN USB-C cable is designed to reduce wear and tear on the cable and on your Type-C smartphones especially ideal for limited space. It's more convenient and more comfortable for playing games, watching videos, reading e-books when you lie on the couch or bed while charging.

Durable and Flexible

5X durable nylon braided cable not only stay tangling-free but also flexible enough to be wrapped up and put in a bag.

Up to 10,000+ bend and 10,000+ plugging and unplugging test ensure this cord a longer lifespan.

Widely Compatibility

Compatible for Samsung Galaxy S10 S10e S10 Plus, Galaxy S9 S9 Plus, Galaxy S8 S8+ Note 9 8, Samsung Galaxy Tab S3 9.7, Samsung Galaxy Fold

Compatible for Apple iPad Pro 11, iPad Pro 12.9 2018

Compatible for LG G5 G6 G7 ThinQ, LG V20 V30 V40 V50 ThinQ

Compatible for Motorola Moto G6, Moto z, z force, z play, Moto z2 force z2 play

Compatible for Nintendo Switch console, Lenovo Zuk Z1, Nokia N1, ZTE Axon 7

Compatible for GoPro Hero 5, hero 7 black hero 7 white hero 7 silver, hero 6 black, gopro hero 2018

Compatible for Microsoft Lumia 950, Lumia 950XL, HTC 10 U12+, Huawei P9 Plus, Huawei P9, OnePlus 2

Important Notes:

1.Can not support thick phone case, Max 0.06 inch phone case.

2.Can not charge the following smartphone at full speed: OnePlus 3 3T 5 5T 6 6T 7 Pro, Google Pixel 2 3, Pixel XL, Pixel 3 XL, Pixel 2 XL, Nexus 5X 6P.

5V/3A Fast Charging

Supports Quick Charge 2.0, QC 3.0 and Samsung AFC fast charging, max: 5V 3A, 9V 2A or 12V 1.5A. Fully charging with your original power charger, as fast as the original cable.

Fast Data Syncing

Date transfer speed is up to 480 Mbps, it will transfer 1GB files in 30 seconds.

Premium Quality

Zinc alloy housing allows you to feel the elegance of the metal and increase its service life, much more resistant to wear and corrosion.

How are ratings calculated?

TOP 1000 REVIEWER
4.0 out of 5 stars Well made cable that works with basic TPU/rubber case - Not for Android Auto
Reviewed in the United States on January 12, 2020
Size: 1.5FTVerified Purchase
Like the other UGREEN cable I own, this is a good cable. The ends are strong, the cable seems strong and flexible, not too thick. Good quality USB 2.0 cable. It does work with a basic TPU case but if the case was a millimeter thicker, it probably wouldn't work (see photos).

My problem was that if I used it with Android Auto, the reason I bought it, Android Auto would randomly disconnect. Through trial and error, I learned that Android Auto (at least in my 2020 car) requires a high-speed data cable - a USB 3.1 cable works. I didn't realize this UGREEN cable was a slower USB 2.0 cable until I asked on this page what USB version it was. UGREEN answered saying it was 2.0. There's tons of text on this product page, including too many phones listed, but the key info on USB version isn't there.

I later learned that 450Mbps is the speed of a USB 2.0 cable. That number is on the page. I suggest UGREEN put "USB 2.0" right there.

It's a good cable, just not for Android Auto. I hope they make one of these with the USB 3 spec. I would buy it.

I'm now left with three options: a) remove the case in order to use this charge cable (not happening), b) modify my case by cutting a bigger cutout around the charge port so that this charger can be more snugly fit when connected, c) keep my unmodified case and just revert back to my old charge cable. Based on the product photos included with this cable, it looked like they had already given consideration to the possibility of using it with a case and had solved for it, but the product photos on this listing don't accurately reflect how the product will fit.

Functionally, this cable seems fine - I just don't have anything I can use it with.

3.0 out of 5 stars WHY IS THIS NOT AVAILABLE IN USB 3.0??!?
Reviewed in the United States on March 28, 2021
Size: 1.5FTVerified Purchase
And longer than 6 feet (2M)? I bought the 1.5' (1/2M) version as a battery bank cable for my Oculus Quest 2. When it arrived and I plugged it in, I fell in love. Instantly I knew I had to buy the longest one available so that I could play games through Oculus Link with it. But there's nothing longer than 6 feet, and they're all only USB 2.

It's fine for battery use, but no Oculus Link kills this for me for anything other than a battery cable. The 90 degree connector is THE BEST connector to plug into a Quest 2's USB C port. It's clean, narrower than EVERY OTHER CONNECTOR out there, and even managed to look better than the official Oculus Link cable, while also sticking out half as far.

This could so easily be the best Oculus Link cable on the market. Instead, it's useless as one, and ends up being an overglorified battery cable. I'm still glad I own one, but If they can make it at least 10' - 16' (3-4M) long and support USB 3. I'd buy 3 immediately.

Reviewed in the United States on March 5, 2020
Size: 1.5FTVerified Purchase
Not that looks are primary factors in cable buying, but this cable really does look great. It feels slightly expensive, and I wish it were USB-C at the other end, not USB-A, but I think I'm just not too satisfied with the current price of USB-C cables in general.

It's good. I'd recommend it.

Timothy R. York
5.0 out of 5 stars Ugreen Makes Top Quality USB Cables
Reviewed in the United States on January 18, 2020
Verified Purchase
If you examine the illustrations of the wires, you will see that the power wire is of a larger gauge than the data lines. This is important for delivering more power to the device, minimizing cable losses, which can matter for finicky devices. You will also see that the USB C connector is extruded, not crimped. The USB A connector is not USB 3.0, apparently, but USB BC1.2 2.0 hubs can deliver a decent amount of power; more than a regular USB hub. The nylon braid is very flexible as well.
Yes, these Ugreen cables cost more, but they are really worth it. It is very well made.
